#=GF CC   The HirA B (Histone regulatory homologue A binding) motif is the
#=GF CC   essential binding interface between HIRA Pfam:PF07569 and ASF1a,
#=GF CC   of approx. 40 residues. It forms an antiparallel beta-hairpin
#=GF CC   that binds perpendicular to the strands of the beta-sandwich of
#=GF CC   ASF1a N-terminal core domain, via beta-sheet, salt bridge and
#=GF CC   van der Waals interactions [1]. The two histone chaperone
#=GF CC   proteins, HIRA and ASF1a, form a heterodimer with histones H3
#=GF CC   and H4. HIRA is the human orthologue of Hir proteins known to
#=GF CC   silence histone gene expression and create transcriptionally
#=GF CC   silent heterochromatin in yeast, flies, plants and humans. The
#=GF CC   yeast CAF1B proteins which bind H3 also carry this motif at
#=GF CC   their very C-terminus. 
